"I'm not going to retire, I'm going to die here, because the volcano is my whole life", Unaynik says, opening his mouth wide, missing several teeth.
Of his five children, the eldest, 30 years old, is also a sulfur transporter.
Time passes, but poverty perpetuates, from generation to generation, one of the most difficult occupations in the world: the work of the human mules of Kawah Ijen.
